description: Nara is an undead teenager on the run from a cult who would have her take over the world. Alyssa is from a stifling high-tech dimension full of people who fear her new powers. What happens when the two become roommates? Chaos ensues, of course! The stars of Josh Howard's Dead@17 and Josh Blaylock's Misplaced team up to fight Zombies, Demons and Interdimensional Soldiers, and look damn good doing it. The catch? Neither one knows of the other girl's power. This series takes place directly after the events of Misplaced #4, and the first Dead@17 mini-series. Â

description:
The final issue of the series moves to world-building rather than profiling characters, and explains various concepts, elements and technology of the Transformers world. Various subjects include sparks, siblings, ships, various factions, fighting arts, energon and so forth.

A one-page comic included at the end helps frame all of the information and depicts a further few familiar faces.

description: The legend of The Transformers begins with the belief of One. Facing a devastating civil war on Cybertron, Optimus Prime faces his first, and greatest, challenge. Before he can deal with the threat posed by Megatron and the Decepticons, the new Autobot leader must look within... and decide if Cybertron is worth saving at all! Witness the internal struggle of a great leader, and the creation of Transformers history! Featuring the return of Simon Furman to Transformers along with a stunning gatefold cover by Don Figueroa!

Cybertron: four million-plus-years before the Transformers came to Earth. As the Autobots prepare for a mass, planet-wide exodus, deep underground, Megatron lays the foundations of future mass-destruction. Go inside one of the darkest, most labyrinthine minds in all creation, as the terrifying truth behind the Decepticons and the war to end all wars is revealed. Be warned: this issue will challenge everything you ever thought you knew about Transformers!

Deep within Cybertron, Optimus Prime faces his first and greatest test: an ordeal by fire against five lethal Decepticon warriors. Wounded, on the run, Prime must plumb personal depths of strength and character he didn't even know he possessed. But even if he survives, waiting in the wings is Megatron...whose agenda is more terrifying and far-reaching than anyone had imagined!

At the very heart of Cybertron, Optimus Prime and Megatron battle, with the future of their own world, and countless others, at stake. But neither combatant is truly ready for the power of the Matrix unleashed! And above, as the Autobot defenses buckle under sustained Decepticon assault, Starscream prepares to unleash the ultimate weapon: Cybertron itself! With shocks, surprises, and a tantalizing hint of things to come in store, you dare not miss this issue!

The action builds to fever pitch, as war rages on all fronts. Above ground, Starscream prepares to activate Megatron's mecha-forming machinery, transforming Cybertron irrevocably, and dooming the Autobots the process, while below Optimus Prime and Megatron battle across time, witnesses to the ultimate future of the Transformer race. Prime's last and best hope may be his most outspoken adversary... Grimlock! Featuring an all-new cover by new Transformers: Armada artist Guido Guidi!

The world-shaking/shattering conclusion! Chaos reigns on Cybertron as the planet itself becomes the Transformers ultimate enemy! But that's only one of Optimus Prime's problems. Megatron now holds the key to the future, secrets that will grant the Decepticon leader dominion over countless worlds. There's only one solution... Megatron must die!

description:
Ten years after the Rapture, the Earth is unprotected by God, and the demonic citizens of hell have flooded our world, enslaving the remaining human population. After saving the life of a runt demon named Bloato, bartender, occultist, and all around arse kicker Bethany Black discovers that God is soon returning to wipe the Earth clean of everything unholy. With the end of the world coming, Bethany and Bloato set out to find the last doorway left into heaven and plead for admission.

Only only way Bethany Black can get into heaven is to raise a little hell!
name: Strangeways Here We Come

description: After years of living under the protection of Belial and The Corridor, Bethany and Bloato have to get the hell outta Dodge and survive the harsh terrain of the American wastelands. A hearty pint of demon-riddled, breakneck, post-Rapture action that leaves Bethany near death. The end of the world was just the beginning.
name: Panic
